cs.NI, cs.MM, cs.SY, cs.IT, cs.CR

Reasoning: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on mobile network resource management for video streaming.
- cs.MM (Multimedia) is also likely as the paper deals with video streaming and quality of experience (QoE) metrics.
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is relevant as the paper proposes a framework for resource management optimization.
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is relevant as the paper deals with optimizing trade-offs between QoE and system utilization cost.
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is less likely but still possible as the paper may touch on security concerns related to mobile network resource management.
